A mobile image cache must balance memory usage, disk persistence, and fast retrieval to avoid re-downloading images on every screen.

**Two-Tier Cache Architecture:**
```
Request → L1: Memory Cache (LRU, fast) → L2: Disk Cache (LRU, persistent) → Network
```

**Java Implementation:**
```java
import android.graphics.Bitmap;
import android.util.LruCache;
import java.io.*;
import java.nio.file.*;

public class ImageCache {
    // L1: Memory cache
    private final LruCache<String, Bitmap> memoryCache;
    // L2: Disk cache
    private final File cacheDir;
    private static final long MAX_DISK_BYTES = 100 * 1024 * 1024; // 100MB

    public ImageCache(Context context) {
        // Use 1/8 of available heap for memory cache
        int maxMemory = (int)(Runtime.getRuntime().maxMemory() / 1024);
        int cacheSize = maxMemory / 8;

        memoryCache = new LruCache<String, Bitmap>(cacheSize) {
            @Override
            protected int sizeOf(String key, Bitmap bitmap) {
                // Size in KB
                return bitmap.getByteCount() / 1024;
            }
            @Override
            protected void entryRemoved(boolean evicted, String key, Bitmap old, Bitmap new_) {
                // When evicted from memory, ensure it's on disk
                if (evicted) saveToDisk(key, old);
            }
        };
        cacheDir = new File(context.getCacheDir(), "images");
        cacheDir.mkdirs();
    }

    public Bitmap get(String url) {
        String key = md5(url);
        // L1 check
        Bitmap bmp = memoryCache.get(key);
        if (bmp != null) return bmp;
        // L2 check
        bmp = loadFromDisk(key);
        if (bmp != null) {
            memoryCache.put(key, bmp); // promote to L1
        }
        return bmp;
    }

    public void put(String url, Bitmap bitmap) {
        String key = md5(url);
        memoryCache.put(key, bitmap);
        saveToDisk(key, bitmap); // async in production
    }

    private void saveToDisk(String key, Bitmap bmp) {
        File file = new File(cacheDir, key);
        try (FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(file)) {
            bmp.compress(Bitmap.CompressFormat.WEBP_LOSSLESS, 100, fos);
        } catch (IOException ignored) {}
    }

    private Bitmap loadFromDisk(String key) {
        File file = new File(cacheDir, key);
        if (!file.exists()) return null;
        file.setLastModified(System.currentTimeMillis()); // LRU tracking
        return BitmapFactory.decodeFile(file.getAbsolutePath());
    }
}
```

**Memory Optimization Techniques:**
```java
// Downsample before decoding (avoid OOM on large images)
public Bitmap decodeSampled(String path, int reqWidth, int reqHeight) {
    BitmapFactory.Options options = new BitmapFactory.Options();
    options.inJustDecodeBounds = true; // don't load pixels, just dimensions
    BitmapFactory.decodeFile(path, options);
    options.inSampleSize = calculateSampleSize(options, reqWidth, reqHeight);
    options.inJustDecodeBounds = false;
    options.inPreferredConfig = Bitmap.Config.RGB_565; // 16-bit vs 32-bit ARGB = 2x less memory
    return BitmapFactory.decodeFile(path, options);
}

private int calculateSampleSize(BitmapFactory.Options opts, int rW, int rH) {
    int inSampleSize = 1;
    if (opts.outHeight > rH || opts.outWidth > rW) {
        while ((opts.outHeight / inSampleSize) > rH ||
               (opts.outWidth / inSampleSize) > rW) {
            inSampleSize *= 2;
        }
    }
    return inSampleSize;
}
```

**Disk Cache LRU Eviction:**
```java
private void evictDiskIfNeeded() {
    File[] files = cacheDir.listFiles();
    if (files == null) return;
    long totalSize = Arrays.stream(files).mapToLong(File::length).sum();
    if (totalSize > MAX_DISK_BYTES) {
        // Sort by last modified (oldest first)
        Arrays.sort(files, Comparator.comparingLong(File::lastModified));
        for (File f : files) {
            totalSize -= f.length();
            f.delete();
            if (totalSize <= MAX_DISK_BYTES * 0.8) break; // evict 20% headroom
        }
    }
}
```

**Production Libraries:**
- Android: Glide, Picasso (both use similar two-tier approach + async loading + placeholder/error images)
- iOS: SDWebImage, Kingfisher (NSCache for L1 — auto-purges on memory warning)
- Web: browser cache (Cache-Control headers) + IndexedDB for PWA offline

**Key Config Parameters:** maxMemoryFraction (1/8 heap), maxDiskMB (50-200MB), imageFormat (WebP saves 30% vs JPEG), transformations cached (cropped/rounded variants stored separately)

Apple Push Notification service (APNs) delivers billions of push notifications daily to iOS, macOS, watchOS, and tvOS devices reliably and securely.

**Architecture:**
```
Provider Server (your backend)
      ↓ HTTP/2 + TLS
  APNs Frontend (connection broker)
      ↓ APNs internal routing
  APNs Backend (message store)
      ↓ persistent connection
  Device (always-on APNs connection)
      ↓
  Delivery to app
```

**Provider → APNs Protocol (HTTP/2):**
```java
// Send push notification to APNs
public class APNsClient {
    private static final String APNS_HOST = "https://api.push.apple.com";

    public HttpResponse<String> sendNotification(
            String deviceToken, String payload, String topic) throws Exception {

        HttpClient client = HttpClient.newBuilder()
            .version(HttpClient.Version.HTTP_2)
            .sslContext(buildSSLContext()) // with Apple cert
            .build();

        String url = APNS_HOST + "/3/device/" + deviceToken;
        String jsonPayload = """    
            {
              \"aps\": {
                \"alert\": {
                  \"title\": \"New Message\",
                  \"body\": \"Alice sent you a message\"
                },
                \"badge\": 1,
                \"sound\": \"default\",
                \"content-available\": 1
              },
              \"custom_key\": \"custom_value\"
            }""";

        HttpRequest request = HttpRequest.newBuilder()
            .uri(URI.create(url))
            .header("apns-topic", topic)       // bundle ID
            .header("apns-priority", "10")      // 10=immediate, 5=background
            .header("apns-push-type", "alert")  // alert|background|voip|complication
            .header("apns-expiration", "0")     // 0=don't store if offline
            .header("authorization", "bearer " + jwtToken())
            .POST(HttpRequest.BodyPublishers.ofString(jsonPayload))
            .build();

        return client.send(request, HttpResponse.BodyHandlers.ofString());
    }
}
```

